title: Topic 006 Question 005
body: You have a Microsoft Teams Phone deployment that has 10 offices. Each office has a Session Border Controller (SBC).
A user reports that she can make internal calls by using the dial pad, but cannot use the dial pad to make external calls.
What is a possible cause of the issue?
options: The user has the incorrect Teams app setup policy applied.
The user has the incorrect voice routing policy applied.
The user is missing a validated emergency address.
Enterprise Voice is disabled for the user.
